review_blob: Canned. Pours a thick, and I mean THICK head. Tastes at first like a cheap Dos XX knock off, then finishes much worse. The disturbing part is the head that begins to resemble styrofoam in a finished glass after a few hours. Will not try again.
Bow down to the king and all its marketing power. Who doesnt like a little beechwood aging now and again? If you buy the king, he never lets you down.
Pours a deep amber with a thin reddish head. Aromas of oats and caramel. Very drinkable with a nice finish. I am a big fan of ambers and this one ranks among my favorites.

This one got me through some tough times in the land of the rising sun. Doesnt need to be said, but it tastes much better over there than in the States. Pours a pale yellow, not much of a discernable scent, slight lacing. Flavor is smooth with, as to be expected, a dry finish. Perfect for sushi and edemame.
In the bottle, nutty aroma. Pours a thin creamy head. Sweet, nutty flavor. simply one of the best brown ales out there.
Creamy white head, dark amber color. The aroma is of toasted bread, caramel malt flavor, this is one you definitely want to get when it is fresh, a great beer overall IMHO.

Got on the cheap at Trader Joes in North Orange County ($4.39 for 6 16oz Cans). Aroma is almost non-existent (yet thankfully not skunky), and flavor is completely non-existent. Ill finish the 6 pack, but I wont be buying this again.

Slight to no aroma, pours a dark gold, mild carbonation. Not too much taste, but what is there is not horrible. Like others have said before me, the true Mexican Bud. Not too bad with a lime and  pinch of salt.

Pours a very creamy rising head, lightly bitter, soft carbonation nearly to the point of non-existent,  flavor is there, but hard to distinguish. A good choice for St. Paddys day if youre not a fan of Guinness.
Canned, also from Trader Joes. (Good Deal) Aromas of alcohol and aluminum. Pours a medium yellow. Light body, fizzy. Inoffensive for the price.

Canned, pours a very thin extremely pale yellow. Metallic taste at first, fades into a urine flavored seltzer water at the end. To be avoided at all costs. A more reasonable choice would be anti-freeze.
